The paper discusses large-scale key-value storage systems and their consistency, which falls under the category of distributed systems (cs.DC). The paper also mentions NoSQL systems, which are commonly used in database systems (cs.DB). The benchmarking technique presented in the paper is minimally disruptive to the system under test, which suggests a focus on operating systems (cs.OS) and software engineering (cs.SE) techniques. Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of existing techniques, which could be considered a critique of current research and falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
